{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}
{{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}}
{{confusing|date=March 2015}}
The '''filmi-ghazal''' is a genre of [[filmi]] based on [[ghazal]] poetry in [[Hindustani language|Hindustani]], used in [[Indian film]]s, especially [[Hindi cinema]] (Bollywood). The filmi-ghazals retain the couplet format and rhyme scheme similar to that in ghazals. However, instead of vocal or instrumental passages as interludes, the filmi-ghazal usually uses precomposed musical pieces.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=dXFBAQAAQBAJ&lpg=PA100&dq=filmi%20ghazal&pg=PA100#v=onepage&q=filmi%20ghazal&f=false | title=More Than Bollywood: Studies in Indian Popular Music | publisher=Oxford University Press | author=Gregory D. Booth, Bradley Shope | year=2014 | pages=100 | isbn=0199928851 |accessdate=21 January 2014}}</ref><ref name="NettlArnold2000">{{cite book|last1=Nettl|first1=Bruno|last2=Arnold|first2=Alison|title=The Garland Encyclopedia of World Music: South Asia : the Indian subcontinent|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZOlNv8MAXIEC&pg=PA534|year=2000|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-8240-4946-1|pages=534}}</ref>

Music directors like [[Madan Mohan (music director)| Madan Mohan]] composed notable filmi-ghazals extensively for [[Muslim social]]s in the 1960s and the 1970s.<ref name="Anantharaman2008">{{cite book|last=Anantharaman|first=Ganesh|title=Bollywood Melodies: A History of the Hindi Film Song|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lmrSLuBwbKkC&pg=PA9|date=January 2008|publisher=Penguin Books India|isbn=978-0-14-306340-7|pages=9}}</ref>

