'''''The [[Freddie Starr]] Comedy Express''''' was a one off television show containing short comedy sketches and standup jokes.<ref>{{cite book |date=1986 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1HGGAAAAMAAJ&q=The+Freddie+Starr+Comedy+Express&dq=The+Freddie+Starr+Comedy+Express&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCUQ6AEwAmoVChMI8o2qo5OgyAIVjYMNCh3j5wKc |title=New Statesman, Volume 112 |page=26 |accessdate=September 30, 2015}}</ref> The show is most famous for the sketch  with Starr spoofing the [[Mick Jagger]] and [[David Bowie]] music video [[Dancing In the Street]].

